SIMPLE: executory
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Executory
<hw>Ex*ec"u*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>executorius</ets>, L. <ets>exsecutorius</ets>: cf.F.
<ets>ex⟦eacute⟧cutoire</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to
administration, or putting the laws in force; executive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The official and <qex>executory</qex> duties of government.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Designed to be executed or carried
into effect in time to come, or to take effect on a future contingency;
<as>as, an <ex>executory</ex> devise, reminder, or estate; an
<ex>executory</ex> contract.</as></def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Executress</ent>⟦br⟧
